trans-unit.source: Loads images from Azure BLOB Storage into a dataset
trans-unit.target: Loads images from Azure BLOB Storage into a dataset

trans-unit.source: You can use the <ui>Image Reader</ui> module to get images from Azure Blob storage and create an image dataset from them.
trans-unit.target: You can use the <ui>Image Reader</ui> module to get images from Azure Blob storage and create an image dataset from them.

trans-unit.source: When you read an image from blob storage using <ui>Image Reader</ui>, the image is represented as a series of numeric values for the red, green, and blue channels, along with the image file name.
trans-unit.target: When you read an image from blob storage using <ui>Image Reader</ui>, the image is represented as a series of numeric values for the red, green, and blue channels, along with the image file name.

trans-unit.source: You can then pass this dataset to the <link xlink:href="401b4f92-e724-4d5a-be81-d5b0ff9bdb33" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Score Model</link> module, and connect a pre-trained image classification model to predict the image type.
trans-unit.target: You can then pass this dataset to the <link xlink:href="401b4f92-e724-4d5a-be81-d5b0ff9bdb33" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Score Model</link> module, and connect a pre-trained image classification model to predict the image type.

trans-unit.source: The <link xlink:href="403eb35a-83b2-4191-a212-7716292c7a5b" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Pretrained image classifier</link> provided in Azure Machine Learning currently supports recognition of faces in frontal view; other image classifiers are not yet available.
trans-unit.target: The <link xlink:href="403eb35a-83b2-4191-a212-7716292c7a5b" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Pretrained image classifier</link> provided in Azure Machine Learning currently supports recognition of faces in frontal view; other image classifiers are not yet available.

trans-unit.source: See the <legacyLink xlink:href="#bkmk_Notes" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Technical Notes</legacyLink> section for a list of the requirements that apply to images.
trans-unit.target: See the <legacyLink xlink:href="#bkmk_Notes" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Technical Notes</legacyLink> section for a list of the requirements that apply to images.

trans-unit.source: Note also that you cannot use image datasets with <link xlink:href="a85a6491-fe78-4461-ba01-2f798a9e3927" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Train Model</link> or <link xlink:href="75fb875d-6b86-4d46-8bcc-74261ade5826" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Cross-Validate Model</link>.
trans-unit.target: Note also that you cannot use image datasets with <link xlink:href="a85a6491-fe78-4461-ba01-2f798a9e3927" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Train Model</link> or <link xlink:href="75fb875d-6b86-4d46-8bcc-74261ade5826" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Cross-Validate Model</link>.

trans-unit.source: <ui>Image Reader</ui> determines the type of an image by reading the first few bytes of the content, not by the file extension.
trans-unit.target: <ui>Image Reader</ui> determines the type of an image by reading the first few bytes of the content, not by the file extension.

trans-unit.source: The following image formats are supported:
trans-unit.target: The following image formats are supported:

trans-unit.source: Each row of the output dataset contains data from one image, ordered as follows:
trans-unit.target: Each row of the output dataset contains data from one image, ordered as follows:

trans-unit.source: The first column contains image names.
trans-unit.target: The first column contains image names.

trans-unit.source: All other columns contain flattened data from the red, green, and blue color channels, in that order.
trans-unit.target: All other columns contain flattened data from the red, green, and blue color channels, in that order.

trans-unit.source: Therefore, depending on the color depth of the image and the image format, there could be many thousands of columns for a single image.
trans-unit.target: Therefore, depending on the color depth of the image and the image format, there could be many thousands of columns for a single image.

trans-unit.source: In the output dataset, the rows are sorted alphabetically by image name.
trans-unit.target: In the output dataset, the rows are sorted alphabetically by image name.

trans-unit.source: This example assumes that you have uploaded multiple images to an Azure blob storage, in a container designated for that purpose only.
trans-unit.target: This example assumes that you have uploaded multiple images to an Azure blob storage, in a container designated for that purpose only.

trans-unit.source: Each image must be fairly small and have the same dimensions and color channels.
trans-unit.target: Each image must be fairly small and have the same dimensions and color channels.

trans-unit.source: Add the <link xlink:href="893f8c57-1d36-456d-a47b-d29ae67f5d84" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Image Reader</link> to your experiment.
trans-unit.target: Add the <link xlink:href="893f8c57-1d36-456d-a47b-d29ae67f5d84" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Image Reader</link> to your experiment.

trans-unit.source: Add the <link xlink:href="403eb35a-83b2-4191-a212-7716292c7a5b" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Pretrained Classifier</link> and the <link xlink:href="401b4f92-e724-4d5a-be81-d5b0ff9bdb33" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Score</link> module.
trans-unit.target: Add the <link xlink:href="403eb35a-83b2-4191-a212-7716292c7a5b" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Pretrained Classifier</link> and the <link xlink:href="401b4f92-e724-4d5a-be81-d5b0ff9bdb33" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Score</link> module.

trans-unit.source: Specify the location of the images by specifying the authentication method, private or public.
trans-unit.target: Specify the location of the images by specifying the authentication method, private or public.

trans-unit.source: If the image set is in a blob that has been configured for public access through <externalLink><linkText>Shared Access Signatures</linkText><linkUri>https://azure.microsoft.com/documentation/articles/storage-dotnet-shared-access-signature-part-1/</linkUri></externalLink>(SAS), type the URL to the container that holds the images.
trans-unit.target: If the image set is in a blob that has been configured for public access through <externalLink><linkText>Shared Access Signatures</linkText><linkUri>https://azure.microsoft.com/documentation/articles/storage-dotnet-shared-access-signature-part-1/</linkUri></externalLink>(SAS), type the URL to the container that holds the images.

trans-unit.source: If the images are stored in a private account in Azure storage, select <ui>Account</ui>, and then type the account name as it appears in the management portal.
trans-unit.target: If the images are stored in a private account in Azure storage, select <ui>Account</ui>, and then type the account name as it appears in the management portal.

trans-unit.source: Paste in the primary or secondary account key, which is provided in the Azure portal.
trans-unit.target: Paste in the primary or secondary account key, which is provided in the Azure portal.

trans-unit.source: For <ui>Path to container</ui>, type just the container name.
trans-unit.target: For <ui>Path to container</ui>, type just the container name.

trans-unit.source: Connect the output of <ui>Image Reader</ui> to the <link xlink:href="401b4f92-e724-4d5a-be81-d5b0ff9bdb33" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Score</link> module.
trans-unit.target: Connect the output of <ui>Image Reader</ui> to the <link xlink:href="401b4f92-e724-4d5a-be81-d5b0ff9bdb33" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Score</link> module.

trans-unit.source: To view the results of the experiment, we recommend that you add the <link xlink:href="1ec722fa-b623-4e26-a44e-a50c6d726223" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">project columns</link> module, and select only these columns:

trans-unit.source: The following requirements apply to images processed by the <ui>Image Reader</ui> module:
trans-unit.target: The following requirements apply to images processed by the <ui>Image Reader</ui> module:

trans-unit.source: All images must be the same shape.
trans-unit.target: All images must be the same shape.

trans-unit.source: All images must have the same color channels.
trans-unit.target: All images must have the same color channels.

trans-unit.source: For example, you cannot mix grayscale images with RBG images.
trans-unit.target: For example, you cannot mix grayscale images with RBG images.

trans-unit.source: There is a limit of 65536 pixels per image.
trans-unit.target: There is a limit of 65536 pixels per image.

trans-unit.source: However, the number of images is not limited.
trans-unit.target: However, the number of images is not limited.

trans-unit.source: If you specify a blob container as the source, the container must not contain blobs.
trans-unit.target: If you specify a blob container as the source, the container must not contain blobs.

trans-unit.source: Ensure that the container contains only images before running the module.
trans-unit.target: Ensure that the container contains only images before running the module.
